# Example configuration for reverse proxy deployments

# When deploying behind a reverse proxy, set the public base URI
# This ensures all OSLC resource URIs use the correct external URL
# rather than the internal container URL

## Example 1: Nginx reverse proxy at example.com/strictdoc
OSLC__PublicBaseUri=https://example.com/strictdoc

## Example 2: Apache reverse proxy at root
# OSLC__PublicBaseUri=https://requirements.example.com

## Example 3: Kubernetes ingress with path prefix
# OSLC__PublicBaseUri=https://apps.company.com/oslc-rm

# If not set, the application will derive URIs from incoming HTTP requests
# which works fine for direct access but may not work correctly behind a proxy
